1
00:00:00,734 --> 00:00:03,537
I'm in love with you, Haru-tan!

2
00:00:03,570 --> 00:00:04,579
I like you.

3
00:00:04,579 --> 00:00:06,025
Are you two having an affair?

4
00:00:06,025 --> 00:00:09,395
You destroyed 30 years of my marriage as if it were nothing.

5
00:00:09,395 --> 00:00:10,453
I'm sorry.

6
00:00:10,453 --> 00:00:14,645
I want us to go back to a mere superior-subordinate relationship.

7
00:00:14,645 --> 00:00:18,445
I'll never hurt you like he does.

8
00:00:18,445 --> 00:00:20,420
I'm staying at Takekawa's.

9
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:22,035
- He's my ex-lover.
- What?

10
00:00:22,035 --> 00:00:24,687
I hope you and Chizu will be happy together.

11
00:00:24,687 --> 00:00:25,702
Don't go.

12
00:00:25,702 --> 00:00:27,835
I'm back.

13
00:00:35,590 --> 00:00:38,710
[Soichi Haruta | Tenku Real Estate Sales Department]

14
00:00:40,390 --> 00:00:42,870
[Ryota Maki | Tenku Real Estate Sales Department]

15
00:00:44,935 --> 00:00:47,670
Hi. Welcome back.

16
00:00:49,612 --> 00:00:52,495
Oh, right. Chinese cabbage...

17
00:00:52,495 --> 00:00:56,095
Teppei asked me to buy Chinese cabbage.

18
00:01:11,245 --> 00:01:13,495
Why did you stop me?

19
00:01:15,353 --> 00:01:17,270
I-I don't know.

20
00:01:17,270 --> 00:01:22,645
I just... don't want you to go.

21
00:01:22,645 --> 00:01:24,702
- Is it because I'm useful around the house?
- That's not it.

22
00:01:24,702 --> 00:01:27,921
- Of course, it is...
- You don't know that.

23
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:32,645
All the things have been all jumbled up in my head.

24
00:01:35,712 --> 00:01:39,320
You and Chizu make a perfect couple.

25
00:01:40,835 --> 00:01:46,120
I've told you Chizu is just my childhood friend.

26
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,621
I don't see her in a romantic way.

27
00:01:47,621 --> 00:01:49,935
Be my lover then.

28
00:01:51,414 --> 00:01:54,011
If so, there wouldn't be a problem, would it?

29
00:01:58,835 --> 00:02:03,835
Haruta, please go out with me.

30
00:02:05,795 --> 00:02:07,395
Okay.

31
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:17,778
Dear God, what does it mean to date another man?

32
00:02:17,778 --> 00:02:21,570
[Ossan's Love]

33
00:02:25,904 --> 00:02:29,496
[Episode 5 | Can You "Come Out"?]

34
00:02:29,496 --> 00:02:31,723
What did I just see?

35
00:02:33,336 --> 00:02:36,345
Hang on, Maki.

36
00:02:36,345 --> 00:02:39,253
I'm not experienced, so I don't really know.

37
00:02:39,253 --> 00:02:46,611
- W-When two guys are dating, what exactly does that entail?
- Pardon?

38
00:02:46,611 --> 00:02:51,102
I mean... forget it.

39
00:02:52,395 --> 00:02:54,095
- You know what?
- I'll take a bath.

40
00:02:54,095 --> 00:02:57,111
Sure. I mean, wait, Maki.

41
00:02:59,445 --> 00:03:06,045
From your point of view, do you see me as your boyfriend,

42
00:03:06,045 --> 00:03:10,578
or am I the girl in this relationship?

43
00:03:10,578 --> 00:03:12,912
Don't be silly.

44
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:16,086
Don't go.

45
00:03:16,086 --> 00:03:19,761
He didn't answer me.

46
00:03:30,145 --> 00:03:32,470
Do you have to take his call?

47
00:03:34,445 --> 00:03:36,265
Calm down.

48
00:03:36,265 --> 00:03:39,695
Why am I so shaken by this?

49
00:03:58,612 --> 00:04:00,635
So sweet.

50
00:04:08,735 --> 00:04:14,670
It's been several days since Maki and I started dating.

51
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:20,728
But what exactly has changed between us since then?

52
00:04:20,728 --> 00:04:22,661
Watch out!

53
00:04:22,661 --> 00:04:24,844
That's dangerous.

54
00:04:37,103 --> 00:04:42,395
- Maki, how about we stagger our arrival time to work?
- Why?

55
00:04:42,395 --> 00:04:47,283
So nobody gets suspicious and starts any crazy rumors.

56
00:04:47,283 --> 00:04:51,400
You don't have to make my lunch for a while.

57
00:04:52,612 --> 00:04:55,035
I understand.

58
00:04:55,035 --> 00:04:57,510
I'll go to the convenience store.

59
00:04:57,510 --> 00:04:59,650
Hey!

60
00:05:04,628 --> 00:05:07,360
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

61
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:10,530
Morning.

62
00:05:11,612 --> 00:05:13,802
- Haruta!
- Good morning.

63
00:05:13,802 --> 00:05:16,961
Mrs. Kurosawa asked for a different realtor.

64
00:05:16,961 --> 00:05:20,828
What did you do to offend her?

65
00:05:20,828 --> 00:05:24,170
Nothing that immediately springs to mind.

66
00:05:24,170 --> 00:05:27,012
Maro will take over. Give him the data.

67
00:05:27,012 --> 00:05:29,360
Sure. Sorry, Sir.

68
00:05:30,003 --> 00:05:33,001
I should keep her up-to-date...

69
00:05:33,001 --> 00:05:36,203
about talking to Director the other day.

70
00:05:36,203 --> 00:05:39,735
And that I flat out rejected him.

71
00:05:40,936 --> 00:05:44,236
Haruta, can we talk?

72
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:46,610
Sure.

73
00:05:47,251 --> 00:05:49,103
Excuse me.

74
00:05:49,103 --> 00:05:50,803
- Come on in.
- Yes.

75
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,360
[Musashi Kurosawa | Sales Department Director]

76
00:05:56,445 --> 00:06:00,295
I really hope this is not about how he still loves me

77
00:06:00,295 --> 00:06:05,045
and can't bear to let me go.

78
00:06:06,735 --> 00:06:11,335
Please treat it as top-secret.

79
00:06:11,335 --> 00:06:14,951
Of course. About what?

80
00:06:14,951 --> 00:06:19,364
The actor Tatsumi Kenzaki wants to look at

81
00:06:19,364 --> 00:06:23,189
the condo Ceres Tower in Kasai as soon as possible.

82
00:06:23,189 --> 00:06:24,390
[Tatsumi Kenzaki]

83
00:06:24,395 --> 00:06:27,521
- Wow, that's Ken-Tatsu.
- Is he famous?

84
00:06:27,521 --> 00:06:31,935
Yes. He just shot a TV show in Antarctica.

85
00:06:31,935 --> 00:06:38,128
His agency is nervous about any leaks to the media.

86
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,495
Or should I ask someone else to do it?

87
00:06:41,495 --> 00:06:46,061
No, Director. Let me do this. I can handle this.

88
00:06:46,061 --> 00:06:49,845
Be extra careful to keep this matter confidential.

89
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:53,290
[Manager's Room]

90
00:06:53,295 --> 00:06:58,112
He's back to normal. So cool.

91
00:06:58,112 --> 00:07:01,003
What the hell was I thinking?

92
00:07:09,336 --> 00:07:11,220
Haru-tan...

93
00:07:12,961 --> 00:07:15,721
Since he was dumped, he can't stop crying.

94
00:07:15,721 --> 00:07:20,728
Was he dumped by his mistress?

95
00:07:20,728 --> 00:07:22,635
Yes.

96
00:07:22,635 --> 00:07:26,761
I simply have lost the will to fight.

97
00:07:27,735 --> 00:07:31,835
In that case, there's no necessity for a divorce.

98
00:07:31,835 --> 00:07:36,536
His heart no longer belongs to me.

99
00:07:38,086 --> 00:07:41,950
Really? That's deep.

100
00:07:42,835 --> 00:07:44,778
What's deep about that?

101
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:52,750
[Ceres Tower Condominium Kasai]

102
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:11,098
Hi, I'm Kenzaki.

103
00:08:12,995 --> 00:08:18,086
I-I'm Haruta, from Tenku Real Estate. Nice to meet you.

104
00:08:18,086 --> 00:08:20,495
It's a pleasure. Sorry for the short notice.

105
00:08:20,495 --> 00:08:23,286
No problem whatsoever!

106
00:08:24,612 --> 00:08:26,162
Sorry.

107
00:08:26,202 --> 00:08:30,742
Please leave everything to me.

108
00:08:30,742 --> 00:08:32,435
This way, please.

109
00:08:34,570 --> 00:08:37,203
This is the place.

110
00:08:37,203 --> 00:08:40,037
It's the penthouse on the top floor.

111
00:08:40,037 --> 00:08:45,428
- Awesome! This is spectacular.
- Yes. Oh, my voice...

112
00:08:45,428 --> 00:08:51,579
To protect tenant privacy, the walkways are invisible from the outside.

113
00:08:51,579 --> 00:08:55,345
Your dedicated elevator only stops at this floor.

114
00:08:55,345 --> 00:08:59,570
- What about if there's a fire?
- Pardon?

115
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:01,935
How do I escape? Parachute?

116
00:09:01,935 --> 00:09:07,903
No, no, no. There's an emergency staircase.

117
00:09:07,903 --> 00:09:10,967
I was in the US for a TV program.

118
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:12,901
The hotel room was equipped with parachutes.

119
00:09:12,934 --> 00:09:16,219
The director told me to jump out as a joke. I was scared to death.

120
00:09:16,219 --> 00:09:20,401
Geez, that's so scary.

121
00:09:20,403 --> 00:09:23,353
The rear entrance. All doors have double locks.

122
00:09:23,353 --> 00:09:26,570
Who cares? I'll only use the front door.

123
00:09:26,570 --> 00:09:27,902
Oh, really?

124
00:09:27,902 --> 00:09:30,103
This way, please.

125
00:09:40,362 --> 00:09:45,661
Lemon Murokawa was super-cute.

126
00:09:45,661 --> 00:09:46,834
Were you always a fan of her?

127
00:09:46,834 --> 00:09:49,595
I didn't really like her in the morning drama,

128
00:09:49,595 --> 00:09:53,303
but what a beauty she was in the flesh.

129
00:09:53,303 --> 00:09:56,978
She's marketed as the "Nation's Little Sister".

130
00:09:56,978 --> 00:10:00,702
The headquarters assigned me to her case a week ago.

131
00:10:00,702 --> 00:10:04,086
But the same building as Ken-Tatsu? What a coincidence.

132
00:10:04,086 --> 00:10:08,395
Well, they're probably dating.

133
00:10:08,395 --> 00:10:12,702
It's a recent trend for stars to live in the same building.

134
00:10:12,735 --> 00:10:15,919
Are you sure about that?

135
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:21,053
That way, they're not exposed to the perils of paparazzi.

136
00:10:21,054 --> 00:10:28,370
What? Does Lemon have a boyfriend?

137
00:10:28,370 --> 00:10:32,986
Oh, well. What's wrong with dating? Ken-Tatsu is a nice guy.

138
00:10:32,986 --> 00:10:38,462
If the media finds out they live in the same building, they're screwed.

139
00:10:38,462 --> 00:10:41,211
I'm sure reporters keep a tab on them constantly.

140
00:10:41,211 --> 00:10:45,019
That means we have a great responsibility.

141
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:49,619
Yes, she's very cautious.

142
00:10:49,619 --> 00:10:52,012
Can you tell me about the security?

143
00:10:52,012 --> 00:10:56,137
Of course, there's a doorman guarding the first floor.

144
00:10:56,137 --> 00:10:59,512
Two concierges are on duty in the foyer 24 hours a day.

145
00:10:59,512 --> 00:11:01,903
All doors are auto locked.

146
00:11:02,587 --> 00:11:04,545
I'll need a card for the elevator?

147
00:11:04,545 --> 00:11:08,253
Yes, and they're only issued to tenants.

148
00:11:09,503 --> 00:11:13,590
- How many security cameras are there?
- Let me check.

149
00:11:13,590 --> 00:11:17,086
Is the road out front a no-parking zone?

150
00:11:18,445 --> 00:11:20,835
- I'll look that up.
- Okay.

151
00:11:21,735 --> 00:11:24,942
It's so unexpected. She appears to be an innocent young lady.

152
00:11:24,942 --> 00:11:27,835
That's just her public persona.

153
00:11:27,835 --> 00:11:31,303
The media will go crazy if they know they're lovers.

154
00:11:31,303 --> 00:11:35,478
So if it's leaked to the media, we are fired?

155
00:11:35,478 --> 00:11:37,953
- On the spot.
- Scary.

156
00:11:37,986 --> 00:11:41,020
Maki, your client is here.

157
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,480
Okay.

158
00:11:44,487 --> 00:11:46,187
Hi, there.

159
00:11:48,378 --> 00:11:49,978
Let's have lunch.

160
00:12:00,211 --> 00:12:02,087
So... maybe dating?

161
00:12:03,195 --> 00:12:05,730
Do you mean the two confidential clients?

162
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:08,950
- Yes, I assume they are.
- No, you and Maki.

163
00:12:10,420 --> 00:12:13,635
How perceptive of him. How did he know?

164
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:17,112
Did Maki make your lunch?

165
00:12:17,112 --> 00:12:18,387
Yes, he did.

166
00:12:18,387 --> 00:12:20,145
Where's the salad?

167
00:12:20,145 --> 00:12:22,095
There's none.

168
00:12:22,095 --> 00:12:24,935
He always made salad for me.

169
00:12:24,935 --> 00:12:26,536
Too bad.

170
00:12:27,420 --> 00:12:31,135
Maybe it's because we're just roommates.

171
00:12:36,835 --> 00:12:38,911
Then set him free.

172
00:12:39,945 --> 00:12:44,057
As long as you're around, he can't let go.

173
00:12:45,835 --> 00:12:49,735
If you don't love him, set him free.

174
00:12:49,735 --> 00:12:51,270
Excuse me?

175
00:12:53,113 --> 00:12:55,871
Don't you know we were dating before?

176
00:12:56,871 --> 00:12:59,321
Yes, Maki told me.

177
00:13:02,535 --> 00:13:08,989
He... can't live without me.

178
00:13:11,462 --> 00:13:14,856
When did you two date?

179
00:13:14,856 --> 00:13:17,795
Just before he joined the firm.

180
00:13:18,410 --> 00:13:21,067
About four years ago.

181
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:23,276
What? Before he joined the company?

182
00:13:23,278 --> 00:13:28,470
When he was a student, he visited me, his alumni, as a part of his job hunting.

183
00:13:29,253 --> 00:13:31,935
Why choose real estate?

184
00:13:31,935 --> 00:13:35,662
No particular reason.

185
00:13:35,662 --> 00:13:38,578
It's not like it's my chosen career.

186
00:13:42,615 --> 00:13:45,306
What do you see yourself doing here?

187
00:13:45,306 --> 00:13:46,990
Well...

188
00:13:48,528 --> 00:13:52,053
His indecisiveness really got my hackles up.

189
00:13:52,053 --> 00:13:54,178
Listen carefully.

190
00:13:54,178 --> 00:13:58,802
I'm wasting valuable time being here to mentor you.

191
00:13:58,802 --> 00:14:00,976
Aren't you being rude?

192
00:14:03,835 --> 00:14:07,919
If you're so reluctant, give up on job hunting. Beat it.

193
00:14:08,635 --> 00:14:10,972
I flat-out told him off.

194
00:14:10,972 --> 00:14:14,935
I can emphasize with that.

195
00:14:14,935 --> 00:14:16,735
Right?

196
00:14:16,735 --> 00:14:20,803
Then, I ran into him again when I was handing out flyers.

197
00:14:20,803 --> 00:14:23,507
There are single-family homes for sale.

198
00:14:23,528 --> 00:14:24,886
Single-family homes...

199
00:14:24,886 --> 00:14:27,136
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

200
00:14:29,654 --> 00:14:31,154
Oh, it's you.

201
00:14:31,982 --> 00:14:33,691
What a nuisance. Go away.

202
00:14:33,691 --> 00:14:35,410
Let me do that.

203
00:14:35,410 --> 00:14:37,040
What?

204
00:14:40,590 --> 00:14:41,835
Hey.

205
00:14:41,835 --> 00:14:43,503
Please.

206
00:14:43,503 --> 00:14:45,560
There you go.

207
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,060
[4LDK House, 12 Minutes Walk from Musashinozaka Station]

208
00:14:53,654 --> 00:14:58,311
No stranger has ever scolded me as severely as you did.

209
00:14:58,311 --> 00:15:00,761
- Are you from Generation X?
- No, I'm a Millennial.

210
00:15:00,781 --> 00:15:02,711
That's the same thing.

211
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:05,570
Here.

212
00:15:11,053 --> 00:15:15,670
All my classmates have found their ideal careers,

213
00:15:15,695 --> 00:15:18,560
but I've got nothing.

214
00:15:18,570 --> 00:15:23,835
However, I read your company introductory essay,

215
00:15:23,835 --> 00:15:25,203
and it really inspired me.

216
00:15:25,203 --> 00:15:28,449
Is that why you paid me an alumni visit to my company?

217
00:15:28,449 --> 00:15:29,903
Yes.

218
00:15:29,903 --> 00:15:32,122
Sorry, but I don't remember what I wrote.

219
00:15:32,138 --> 00:15:34,734
You wrote, "it's not about doing the job you love,

220
00:15:34,735 --> 00:15:37,278
you should learn to love your job."

221
00:15:40,587 --> 00:15:43,235
- I still don't remember.
- What?

222
00:15:43,235 --> 00:15:47,724
He fell for me, and applied to our company.

223
00:15:47,735 --> 00:15:50,135
But you two split up, didn't you?

224
00:15:50,712 --> 00:15:55,228
He worked at the headquarters, and I worked at a branch.

225
00:15:55,228 --> 00:15:58,095
Our different lifestyles have driven us apart.

226
00:15:59,878 --> 00:16:04,835
But I'll never make the same mistake twice.

227
00:16:10,278 --> 00:16:12,245
I'm begging you.

228
00:16:12,278 --> 00:16:14,645
Please give up on Maki.

229
00:16:14,645 --> 00:16:16,621
Please raise your head. Someone might see us.

230
00:16:16,654 --> 00:16:18,495
I beg you, please.

231
00:16:18,495 --> 00:16:23,836
Without Maki, life's not worth living.

232
00:16:23,836 --> 00:16:29,435
I need him. Please set him free!

233
00:16:30,153 --> 00:16:32,178
He wants me to leave Maki?

234
00:16:32,178 --> 00:16:36,361
He wants a reconciliation, so I have to leave Maki?

235
00:16:37,003 --> 00:16:39,235
I don't want to do that.

236
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:43,719
Why don't I? Why?

237
00:16:56,336 --> 00:16:59,378
Thanks to you, we're settling back in.

238
00:16:59,378 --> 00:17:02,566
The bar reopens tomorrow.

239
00:17:02,566 --> 00:17:03,835
Congrats.

240
00:17:03,835 --> 00:17:05,419
Thanks.

241
00:17:09,073 --> 00:17:11,815
Did you go to Dreamland with Maro?

242
00:17:11,815 --> 00:17:15,743
No, something came up at work and I had to cancel.

243
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:17,253
Is that right?

244
00:17:17,253 --> 00:17:20,928
I feel bad for him. I must make up for it.

245
00:17:20,928 --> 00:17:23,299
No need, don't overthink it.

246
00:17:23,299 --> 00:17:25,733
That's not how things work.

247
00:17:25,746 --> 00:17:27,928
Really?

248
00:17:32,961 --> 00:17:36,162
Maro and Chizu are getting closer lately.

249
00:17:36,162 --> 00:17:38,702
What a joke.

250
00:17:38,702 --> 00:17:42,345
Sooner or later, he'll realize her flaws.

251
00:17:42,345 --> 00:17:46,228
When she cooks eggs, she leaves the shell in.

252
00:17:47,253 --> 00:17:50,262
Haruta, how about we go shopping tomorrow?

253
00:17:50,262 --> 00:17:52,695
- Do you need something?
- No, it's for you.

254
00:17:52,695 --> 00:17:55,602
- All your clothes are freaking lame.
- Seriously?

255
00:17:55,602 --> 00:18:00,527
I don't like it when my lover looks so uncool.

256
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:05,420
So I'm his lover, now?

257
00:18:05,420 --> 00:18:10,679
What if our acquaintances see us together on the street?

258
00:18:10,679 --> 00:18:14,403
So what? It's normal for two guys to go shopping.

259
00:18:14,403 --> 00:18:16,911
Right. I guess he's right.

260
00:18:17,735 --> 00:18:19,290
[Divorce Papers]

261
00:18:19,290 --> 00:18:20,990
Sign it.

262
00:18:23,461 --> 00:18:25,236
Well...

263
00:18:25,236 --> 00:18:26,928
