- Wear it properly.

284
00:20:23,545 --> 00:20:25,977
It looks weird.

285
00:20:26,999 --> 00:20:28,799
It looks like a skirt.

286
00:20:28,799 --> 00:20:31,784
You look great. Look here.

287
00:20:35,183 --> 00:20:37,899
From now on, I should let you choose my clothes.

288
00:20:37,899 --> 00:20:41,317
You're old enough to know what suits you.

289
00:20:41,317 --> 00:20:43,901
- Don't want to!
- Don't say that.

290
00:20:43,901 --> 00:20:47,150
Hungry? Let's go grab some ramen.

291
00:20:47,150 --> 00:20:49,626
There's this one shop I want to take you.

292
00:20:49,626 --> 00:20:51,210
Let's go. Wait...

293
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:53,590
which way is it?

294
00:20:56,609 --> 00:20:58,534
Wait up.

295
00:21:00,150 --> 00:21:01,559
Let's eat.

296
00:21:01,559 --> 00:21:04,267
You don't take photos?

297
00:21:04,267 --> 00:21:05,998
No, I'm not on Instagram.

298
00:21:05,999 --> 00:21:09,234
Really? You should.

299
00:21:10,609 --> 00:21:13,467
Okay, then. I'll try it.

300
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:15,559
I can set up your account.

301
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:22,050
Oh, my. So creepy.

302
00:21:22,050 --> 00:21:23,259
What's wrong?

303
00:21:23,259 --> 00:21:27,059
Look, Haruta just sent me this. This is insane.

304
00:21:27,059 --> 00:21:29,109
What a smug look.

305
00:21:29,109 --> 00:21:31,651
He's all dressed up.

306
00:21:31,651 --> 00:21:34,551
He's clueless when it comes to fashion.

307
00:21:34,551 --> 00:21:36,626
He wears a hoodie over a hoodie,

308
00:21:36,626 --> 00:21:39,718
and leather shoes without socks.

309
00:21:39,718 --> 00:21:42,367
You seem to know a lot about him. That's cool.

310
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:46,034
There's no way he chose that by himself.

311
00:21:46,034 --> 00:21:49,442
What's going on? Isn't it hilarious?

312
00:21:51,526 --> 00:21:53,890
Thank you for waiting. Please come inside.

313
00:21:53,890 --> 00:21:55,910
That's nice.

314
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:06,590
- There you go.
- Hang on.

315
00:22:08,259 --> 00:22:09,651
[You look creepy. I'm enjoying pancakes at Omotesando.]

316
00:22:09,651 --> 00:22:12,609
Chizu's nearby. Shall we meet up later?

317
00:22:12,609 --> 00:22:16,167
Yeah, why not?

318
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:18,892
But she's with Maro.

319
00:22:25,999 --> 00:22:27,725
She's not picking up.

320
00:22:32,025 --> 00:22:34,775
Sorry.

321
00:22:34,775 --> 00:22:36,966
No need to stand so close.

322
00:22:36,966 --> 00:22:41,100
You never know who's watching. There might be someone we know.

323
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:43,475
So what if they see us?

324
00:22:43,475 --> 00:22:48,517
- What?
- Are you ashamed to be seen with me?

325
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:54,859
That's not what I meant. How should I say this?

326
00:22:58,209 --> 00:23:00,700
- Hello?
- It's an emergency!

327
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:05,966
- What?
- Ms. Murokawa is asking you to come to the condo right away.

328
00:23:05,966 --> 00:23:07,442
Right now?

329
00:23:07,442 --> 00:23:08,950
I know it's your day off,

330
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:12,275
but please rush over.

331
00:23:12,275 --> 00:23:14,342
Okay, I will.

332
00:23:15,899 --> 00:23:17,700
I'm sorry, it's work. I have to go.

333
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:19,700
What? Wait...

334
00:23:23,654 --> 00:23:26,471
How about we go to the aquarium?

335
00:23:28,099 --> 00:23:31,900
One time, back in high school,

336
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:34,400
Haruta was attacked by a seal at the aquarium.

337
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:37,242
It took him two months for the scars to heal.

338
00:23:39,621 --> 00:23:40,975
Maro?

339
00:23:40,975 --> 00:23:44,083
Sorry, I have plans right after this.

340
00:23:44,083 --> 00:23:45,684
- Let's say goodbye here.
- What?

341
00:23:45,684 --> 00:23:51,067
I need to meet up with three or four girls on my day off to satisfy them all.

342
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:54,142
Satisfy them all? How rude.

343
00:23:54,142 --> 00:23:57,260
You're the one who's being rude.

344
00:23:57,260 --> 00:24:02,120
- What?
- This whole time you've only talked about Haruta.

345
00:24:02,859 --> 00:24:05,699
Perhaps, you didn't even notice?

346
00:24:07,317 --> 00:24:09,000
I'm sorry.

347
00:24:12,692 --> 00:24:14,900
Let me give you a piece of advice.

348
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:18,659
Haruta is too thick-headed.

349
00:24:18,659 --> 00:24:21,999
He'll never get it, unless you tell him.

350
00:24:24,584 --> 00:24:26,050
Bye.

351
00:24:36,759 --> 00:24:38,699
Please.

352
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,292
Everything seems in order.

353
00:24:46,125 --> 00:24:47,967
He really upseted me.

354
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:50,975
Why is a civil servant so unfriendly?

355
00:24:50,975 --> 00:24:55,718
It was a major event in life, he should have said something.

356
00:24:55,718 --> 00:25:00,000
Some words of comfort or sympathy would've been nice.

357
00:25:03,176 --> 00:25:05,866
- What's so funny?
- Well...

358
00:25:05,866 --> 00:25:10,609
You said the exact same thing when we got married.

359
00:25:10,609 --> 00:25:14,384
You complained the clerk didn't offer congratulations.

360
00:25:14,384 --> 00:25:16,600
- Did I?
- Yes.

361
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:19,542
It's been so long. I forgot.

362
00:25:20,651 --> 00:25:23,359
I know. Let's go there.

363
00:25:23,359 --> 00:25:24,685
Where?

364
00:25:24,685 --> 00:25:26,342
This way.

365
00:25:26,342 --> 00:25:29,020
- What?
- Come on!

366
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:33,320
[Ossan's Love]

367
00:25:37,167 --> 00:25:39,234
Haruta!

368
00:25:40,150 --> 00:25:41,790
Hi, there.

369
00:25:42,759 --> 00:25:46,718
- Why the seaside?
- Sorry. The ocean seems furious.

370
00:25:46,718 --> 00:25:48,661
By the way, where's Maro?

371
00:25:49,489 --> 00:25:51,089
He left.

372
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:54,378
Did he dump you already?

373
00:25:54,378 --> 00:25:55,900
Will you shut up!

374
00:25:55,900 --> 00:25:59,192
What's with these weird clothes, anyway?

375
00:25:59,192 --> 00:26:02,899
Maki chose them. If you don't like them, tell him.

376
00:26:02,899 --> 00:26:04,400
Where is Maki?

377
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,442
He had urgent work.

378
00:26:12,692 --> 00:26:17,759
We used to come here with Teppei in summer, remember?

379
00:26:17,759 --> 00:26:21,493
I built that sandcastle and you destroyed it.

380
00:26:21,493 --> 00:26:23,899
I was furious.

381
00:26:23,899 --> 00:26:26,567
I remember that.

382
00:26:31,620 --> 00:26:33,330
Go.

383
00:26:36,621 --> 00:26:39,012
Haruta is too thick-headed.

384
00:26:39,012 --> 00:26:42,238
He'll never get it, unless you tell him.

385
00:26:45,564 --> 00:26:47,712
- Listen, Haruâ€”
- Chizu.

386
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:52,836
Sorry. You go ahead.

387
00:26:52,836 --> 00:26:55,371
No, you first.

388
00:27:07,836 --> 00:27:09,536
You see...

389
00:27:11,234 --> 00:27:15,400
Maki and I are dating now.

390
00:27:17,730 --> 00:27:20,000
What?

391
00:27:21,209 --> 00:27:24,499
He asked me and I said yes.

392
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:30,004
But nothing has actually changed between us.

393
00:27:30,004 --> 00:27:34,178
I just thought I should tell you.

394
00:27:35,776 --> 00:27:37,599
I see.

395
00:27:38,292 --> 00:27:40,060
That's great.

396
00:27:40,776 --> 00:27:44,367
You're the first person I've told about it.

397
00:27:44,367 --> 00:27:46,259
Really?

398
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:51,584
You know...

399
00:27:51,584 --> 00:27:58,820
I, for one, don't want anyone to know about it.

400
00:27:58,820 --> 00:28:04,567
And that seemed to really upset Maki.

401
00:28:06,751 --> 00:28:08,499
I see.

402
00:28:08,499 --> 00:28:10,999
So you're a couple now?

403
00:28:10,999 --> 00:28:13,309
Do you love him?

404
00:28:13,999 --> 00:28:15,876
Well, I...

405
00:28:18,849 --> 00:28:21,795
I guess I do.

406
00:28:23,634 --> 00:28:26,809
[Chizu & Haruta Love Forever]

407
00:28:30,442 --> 00:28:33,267
Right. Chizu, what did you

408
00:28:33,267 --> 00:28:36,251
want to tell me?

409
00:28:36,251 --> 00:28:39,109
Wait. What was it?

410
00:28:39,109 --> 00:28:42,367
I've completely forgotten what I wanted to say.

411
00:28:42,367 --> 00:28:44,267
How is that possible?

412
00:28:44,267 --> 00:28:46,925
Stop that! It's cold.

413
00:28:49,810 --> 00:28:51,560
- Take this.
- It's cold.

414
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:53,420
Stop it!

415
00:28:56,442 --> 00:28:58,883
Wait a second.

416
00:29:02,729 --> 00:29:05,303
What is it, Maki?

417
00:29:07,042 --> 00:29:09,025
Right now?

418
00:29:24,999 --> 00:29:28,767
Do you remember this place?

419
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:31,476
It's where you proposed to me.

420
00:29:31,476 --> 00:29:33,126
Of course, I do.

421
00:29:36,711 --> 00:29:39,446
It brings back memories.

422
00:29:50,899 --> 00:29:54,360
Let's say farewell here.

423
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:55,770
What?

424
00:29:56,776 --> 00:30:00,317
I've enjoyed our final date.

425
00:30:01,999 --> 00:30:03,499
Me, too.

426
00:30:05,526 --> 00:30:08,010
You dumped me for Haruta,

427
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:11,200
so make sure you win his heart.

428
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,900
Choko,

429
00:30:19,234 --> 00:30:21,300
for the last 30 years...

430
00:30:23,492 --> 00:30:25,067
Thank you.

431
00:30:29,275 --> 00:30:32,267
Why are you so formal?

432
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:36,799
Farewell.

433
00:31:04,676 --> 00:31:08,385
- Sorry about this.
- What's the problem?

434
00:31:08,385 --> 00:31:13,320
I'm sorry, but I'm too scared

435
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:15,600
for the both of us to live here.

436
00:31:16,899 --> 00:31:18,342
Sorry, Haruta.

437
00:31:18,342 --> 00:31:21,866
Actually, we have been dating.

438
00:31:21,866 --> 00:31:24,850
Yes, we figured that much.

439
00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:28,034
Honestly, I don't care if the words get out.

440
00:31:28,034 --> 00:31:29,585
Let's not sneak around.

441
00:31:29,585 --> 00:31:32,966
But that would ruin my career.

442
00:31:32,966 --> 00:31:35,192
This would cause great inconvenience to many people.

443
00:31:35,192 --> 00:31:37,792
Not if I explain it to them.

444
00:31:37,792 --> 00:31:40,790
Why would we be criticized for loving someone?

445
00:31:40,790 --> 00:31:43,130
We're not committing adultery.

446
00:31:43,130 --> 00:31:44,766
Let's be open about it.

447
00:31:44,766 --> 00:31:47,950
That may work for you, but it'll destroy my career.

448
00:31:47,950 --> 00:31:49,966
Those are nothing but pretty words.

449
00:31:49,966 --> 00:31:51,409
You're right.

450
00:31:51,409 --> 00:31:55,799
A secret love can never last.

451
00:31:56,592 --> 00:31:59,966
Then we should break up.

452
00:31:59,966 --> 00:32:03,284
Wait, wait. Let's think rationally.

453
00:32:03,284 --> 00:32:04,817
Listen...

454
00:32:07,609 --> 00:32:09,234
actually,

455
00:32:10,109 --> 00:32:12,651
we're dating, too.

456
00:32:12,651 --> 00:32:14,966
Really? What?

457
00:32:14,966 --> 00:32:17,259
Dating?

458
00:32:17,259 --> 00:32:20,866
What? A guy dating another guy?

459
00:32:20,866 --> 00:32:24,699
Yes, so...

460
00:32:24,699 --> 00:32:30,400
Considering your career, I fully understand you want to keep it a secret.

461
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:31,310
At the same time,

462
00:32:31,310 --> 00:32:35,317
I also understand your wish to be open.

463
00:32:38,442 --> 00:32:40,766
People will always talk.

464
00:32:40,766 --> 00:32:47,120
I personally think what's important to you matters the most

465
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,251
at the end.

466
00:32:54,799 --> 00:32:56,783
Sorry.

467
00:32:59,192 --> 00:33:01,692
Look, paparazzi!

468
00:33:03,330 --> 00:33:06,300
You there! Hey!

469
00:33:06,300 --> 00:33:08,909
I'll go get him.

470
00:33:17,651 --> 00:33:19,899
Here is your refill.

471
00:33:19,899 --> 00:33:23,100
What an unusual duo.

472
00:33:26,309 --> 00:33:29,409
Why aren't I good enough for her?

473
00:33:30,818 --> 00:33:35,760
I am not inferior to him in any way.

474
00:33:36,899 --> 00:33:40,217
I'm better looking, and have a better personality.

475
00:33:41,759 --> 00:33:43,199
I have a gorgeous face.

476
00:33:44,409 --> 00:33:47,067
Cheer up, kiddo.

477
00:33:47,899 --> 00:33:49,532
Thanks.

478
00:33:49,532 --> 00:33:54,099
I prepared the bacon-wrapped durian for you.

479
00:33:54,099 --> 00:33:57,526
What's this? We didn't order it.

480
00:34:07,009 --> 00:34:09,967
You know, I...

481
00:34:09,967 --> 00:34:13,090
wanted to show him my mature side,

482
00:34:13,090 --> 00:34:17,400
so I offered him a divorce.

483
00:34:27,551 --> 00:34:29,820
However...

484
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:33,510
here I am, over 50 years old.

485
00:34:35,125 --> 00:34:38,892
And I'm not even close to maturing.

486
00:34:40,234 --> 00:34:43,392
Why doesn't he love me?

487
00:34:43,392 --> 00:34:45,984
Every time I see him,

488
00:34:48,250 --> 00:34:50,030
it's the only thing

489
00:34:51,610 --> 00:34:53,600
I can think of.

490
00:34:55,526 --> 00:34:57,076
I'll go wash up.

491
00:34:58,560 --> 00:34:59,850
What are you doing?

492
00:34:59,850 --> 00:35:02,800
Good girl. You did your best.

493
00:35:03,749 --> 00:35:06,657
- What?
- Stay still.

494
00:35:06,657 --> 00:35:10,700
When you hear the heartbeat,

495
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:12,670
don't you feel comforted?

496
00:35:16,584 --> 00:35:19,034
Don't tease an old lady.

497
00:35:20,442 --> 00:35:24,317
You just told me you're not mature.

498
00:35:26,175 --> 00:35:28,342
Are you crazy?

499
00:35:49,407 --> 00:35:53,050
Damn it! Damn it!

500
00:35:53,999 --> 00:35:56,109
No luck?

501
00:35:56,109 --> 00:35:58,525
Damn it!

502
00:36:00,376 --> 00:36:05,118
That photo will be the front page in all the tabloids.

503
00:36:05,118 --> 00:36:09,799
That sucks. What do we do now?

504
00:36:16,042 --> 00:36:17,917
Sorry about earlier.

505
00:36:19,676 --> 00:36:22,899
For telling them about us without your permission.

506
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:29,367
I don't mind it. I feel apologetic because...

507
00:36:29,367 --> 00:36:32,899
Take it at your own pace.

508
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:35,090
Not a boyfriend in name only,

509
00:36:35,090 --> 00:36:38,890
I'll try harder to win your heart.

510
00:36:46,899 --> 00:36:48,400
Maki.

511
00:36:51,234 --> 00:36:53,276
I'm not ashamed.

512
00:36:54,899 --> 00:37:01,390
I'm not at all ashamed of being with you.

513
00:37:17,317 --> 00:37:19,034
Big news, everyone!

514
00:37:19,034 --> 00:37:22,326
A joint press conference is starting!

515
00:37:22,326 --> 00:37:25,392
Come watch it.

516
00:37:25,392 --> 00:37:28,999
I, Tatsumi Kenzaki,

517
00:37:28,999 --> 00:37:33,420
have been in a relationship with Miss Lemon Murokawa

518
00:37:33,420 --> 00:37:36,986
with marriage in mind.

519
00:37:36,986 --> 00:37:39,412
- He said it.
- He sure did.

520
00:37:39,412 --> 00:37:43,292
Wasn't it supposed to be top secret?

521
00:37:44,364 --> 00:37:45,800
With that said,

522
00:37:46,770 --> 00:37:49,330
we no longer want to live our lives

523
00:37:49,331 --> 00:37:53,119
hiding ourselves in lies.

524
00:37:53,809 --> 00:37:57,866
To all my fans and staffs

525
00:37:57,866 --> 00:38:01,020
who have been supporting me,

526
00:38:01,020 --> 00:38:05,460
I apologize for all the troubles and concerns I have caused.

527
00:38:07,025 --> 00:38:11,970
But I am in love with Mr. Kenzaki.

528
00:38:12,759 --> 00:38:18,520
I'll work harder to earn your further support.

529
00:38:19,567 --> 00:38:24,692
What prompted you to reveal your relationship now?

530
00:38:26,217 --> 00:38:30,559
The reason we decided to make this public announcement,

531
00:38:30,559 --> 00:38:33,643
is because we recently met a lovely couple.

532
00:38:33,643 --> 00:38:36,790
Actually, it's a couple of two men.

533
00:38:36,790 --> 00:38:38,700
- But...
- Stop right there.

534
00:38:38,700 --> 00:38:41,066
- Why did you do that?
- You!

535
00:38:41,066 --> 00:38:44,000
- That was the highlight.
